        {
          "id": "972cf2a23ff2_2",
          "href": null,
          "name": "86ef",
          "text": "Daniel C. Wahl and Stephan Harding at Schumacher College, 2007",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "H4"
        },
        {
          "id": "972cf2a23ff2_3",
          "href": null,
          "name": "e2fc",
          "text": "I owe a huge debt of gratitude to Stephan Harding. During my time on the Masters in Holistic Science at Schumacher College (2001–2002) his teaching and friendship deeply influenced my way of thinking and has affected my life path ever since.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 122,
              "href": "https://www.schumachercollege.org.uk/holistic-science-msc-pg-cert",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 73,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "972cf2a23ff2_4",
          "href": null,
          "name": "1f05",
          "text": "Stephan set up the MSc. in Holistic Science together with Professor Brian Goodwin in 1998, after already having been instrumental in the foundation of Schumacher College which led to his close friendship and collaboration with James Lovelock on Gaia Theory.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "972cf2a23ff2_5",
          "href": null,
          "name": "2e23",
          "text": "In 2007, I visited Stephan and Brian at Schumacher College as part of my work of co-directing Findhorn College at the time. I took the opportunity to interview my old teachers and mentors on that visit and the clips below are the result of these conversations (which were lost on a hard drive until rediscovered them recently — here the link to the interview with Brian Goodwin).",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 377,
              "href": "https://hackernoon.com/a-science-of-qualities-experiencing-the-world-coming-into-being-living-on-the-edge-of-chaos-d54b6dce4c2c",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 349,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "972cf2a23ff2_6",
          "href": null,
          "name": "33a1",
          "text": "In this first video, Stephan tells the story of how Schumacher College and the MSc. in Holistic Science were started and then we move on to his work and friendship with James Lovelock. Stephan offers a very personal account of this remarkable scientist who co-founded the field of Gaia Theory with Lynn Margulis.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "972cf2a23ff2_7",
          "href": null,
          "name": "76c3",
          "text": "",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": {
            "mediaResource": {
              "href": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=H6DmgG1kiLc&t=13s"
            }
          },
          "layout": "INSET_CENTER",
          "markups": [],
          "type": "IFRAME"
        },
        {
          "id": "972cf2a23ff2_8",
          "href": null,
          "name": "977b",
          "text": "In the second video Stephan talks about the four-fold way of knowing mapped out by C.G. Jung (thinking, sensing, feeling, intuiting) which he used in his acclaimed book ‘Animate Earth’ to weave a bridge between Gaia Theory and Deep Ecology.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 183,
              "href": "http://www.greenbooks.co.uk/animate-earth",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 170,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "972cf2a23ff2_9",
          "href": null,
          "name": "8f39",
          "text": "Stephan speaks of what happens to people when they have the experience of being “Gaia-ed”, and how such an embodied experience of being alive in Earth as an animate being can be profoundly transformative and revelatory. He regards these kinds of experiences as essential to the deeper shifts in worldview and participation that need to underly the transition to sustainable and regenerative cultures.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "972cf2a23ff2_10",
          "href": null,
          "name": "bab5",
          "text": "We also explore the work of Arne Ness, another mentor and collaborator of Stephan’s. “Deep Ecology is about a deep experience of the sentient nature of the world.” … and how to act from that connection.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "972cf2a23ff2_11",
          "href": null,
          "name": "fe5e",
          "text": "",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": {
            "mediaResource": {
              "href": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IRH3l5KmzAM"
            }
          },
          "layout": "INSET_CENTER",
          "markups": [],
          "type": "IFRAME"
        },
        {
          "id": "972cf2a23ff2_12",
          "href": null,
          "name": "8d07",
          "text": "In the third video Stephan answers my question about where he sees the role of permaculture and the ecovillage movement in the transition towards living sustainably in intimate relationship with and as an Animate Earth.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 202,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 199,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "972cf2a23ff2_13",
          "href": null,
          "name": "04fd",
          "text": "He permaculture and ecovillage pioneers as those who are actively exploring pathways to a viable future where the way we live expresses our deep connection and interdependence with the cycles of a living Earth.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "972cf2a23ff2_14",
          "href": null,
          "name": "7318",
          "text": "",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": {
            "mediaResource": {
              "href": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=H3pNr3Z2fu8"
            }
          },
          "layout": "INSET_CENTER",
          "markups": [],
          "type": "IFRAME"
        },
        {
          "id": "972cf2a23ff2_15",
          "href": null,
          "name": "8760",
          "text": "Having seen many ups and downs in the relationship between Schumacher College and the charity that supports it to do its work — Dartington Trust — this video is somewhat timely today, as there has recently been another upheaval and restructuring that the Trust forced on the college.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "972cf2a23ff2_16",
          "href": null,
          "name": "57f6",
          "text": "Here Stephan outlines his vision (from 2007) for the future of Schumacher College and the Dartington Estate. Some of it did come to pass in the year’s since and other aspects are still aspirational yet possibly even more urgently needed then back then.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "972cf2a23ff2_17",
          "href": null,
          "name": "5bbd",
          "text": "",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": {
            "mediaResource": {
              "href": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uXOEO_tEcP0"
            }
          },
          "layout": "INSET_CENTER",
          "markups": [],
          "type": "IFRAME"
        },
        {
          "id": "972cf2a23ff2_18",
          "href": null,
          "name": "97bd",
          "text": "This last video is another 90 second re-take on the role of permaculture and ecovillages which I asked Stephan to comment on. He also highlights the critical importance of having an experience of wilderness as he stresses the overall importance of experiential learning.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "972cf2a23ff2_19",
          "href": null,
          "name": "ce59",
          "text": "",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": {
            "mediaResource": {
              "href": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=C3oAZIVb4HQ"
            }
          },
          "layout": "INSET_CENTER",
          "markups": [],
          "type": "IFRAME"
        },
        {
          "id": "972cf2a23ff2_20",
          "href": null,
          "name": "3430",
          "text": "I hope you will enjoy the videos and share them widely.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
